What I wrote (and you've experienced) was the answer. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /> <br /><br />As you said: &quot;<em>- Right-click on Start &gt; Settings &gt; Start Menu Style tab &gt; Classic with two columns</em>&quot; and you'll have the same if you chose &quot;Classic&quot;, in both cases you have three rows of tabs.<br />Then you said: &quot;<em>If, instead, I choose &quot;Windows 7 style&quot;, I still only see two rows of tabs.</em>&quot; and these are the settings available for that style.<br /><br />As a side note, in most cases (not all), you can swap the menu style, make the changes, then swap it back and some settings are maintained.<br /><br />Someone could correct me if I'm wrong, but, for what I know, the tabs are dependent on the menu style you chose.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=16365">fonpaolo</a> — Tue Nov 29, 2016 9:51 am</p><hr />
